"name":"UX"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"This was discovered during work with a partner.\r\n\r\nPartner accidentally bundled image with wrong credentials (x.509 certs). He was able to upload it and register an emi out of it. When he launched an instance it went from pending to terminated. the user had no idea why?\r\n\r\nThe cloud administrator logs in to the cloud to debug his problem. The first thing he did was to go to the NC and check the nc.log for failure. He found that the NC was trying to download the image and then suddenly failed with a 404. This means the image was not there in walrus cache. He then logs in to the Walrus machine and checks\r\n\r\nWalrus was not able to decrypt the image.\r\n\r\nOne need to look at the cloud-output.log file which has:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n2014-02-28 13:50:18 ERROR | [CorrelationId: 325750d2-4bb4-4f34-8d88-c058efdd00d7 | Account: 556996172545] Decryption failed for: XXXX-ab6d8171-3414-ecc-cluster-1/tmp3-bundle-vol-centos6-20140228153105.manifest.xml due to AES params\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis is a big usability issue.\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"bundle image with wrong creds instance goes pending -> terminated","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=tjcramer","name":"tjcramer","key":"tjcramer","accountId":"557058:e076cf45-80ca-4b67-befb-7b0c21f32739","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/65e7a5c18fc469f1978f6367993c3bf0?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dtjcramer%26avatarId%3D10401%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/65e7a5c18fc469f1978f6367993c3bf0?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dt